  {
    "id": "1813217387652477073",
    "text": "Just watched “Hillbilly Elegy” — movie based on J.D. Vance’s autobiography.\n\nTough life growing up in a lower-class white family in deindustrialized Ohio/Kentucky.\n\nNot to mention a dysfunctional family with a drug addict mom.\n\nIn a normal world, a politician with such background would be a wonderful person who would do great things for the poor and the working class.\n\nBut we live in a world controlled by psychopathic network of oligarchs, bankers, corporations, lobbyists, handlers and media. \n\nHowever nice a guy J.D. is, he will be restrained by the dystopian reality in Washington DC.",
    "author": {
      "id": "1510780961281409025",
      "name": "S.L. Kanthan",
      "screenName": "Kanthan2030",
      "profileImageUrl": "https://pbs.twimg.com/profile_images/1733778481824329728/N3K8LyQz_normal.jpg",
      "verified": true
    },
    "metrics": {
      "likes": 954,
      "retweets": 174,
      "replies": 117,
      "quotes": 16,
      "views": 80303,
      "bookmarks": 97
    },
    "createdAt": "Tue Jul 16 14:21:27 +0000 2024",
    "createdAtLocal": "2024-07-16 22:21",
    "createdAtISO": "2024-07-16T14:21:27+00:00",
    "media": [
      {
        "type": "photo",
