  {
    "id": "1813322273807642654",
    "text": "How J.D. Vance saved my life!\n\nMost y'all don't know this, but I have deep roots to Appalachia KY/TN and briefly worked in Cincy/Dayton area.  Many years ago, I'd married a gal from up north.  Real high flutin folks.  My family was poor, had accents, and didn't dress fancy.  Her momma never would accept my family, and my wife quickly became the same.  J.D. Vance's book Hillbilly Elegy had just came out, and her momma bought it for my wife to \"better understand\" me and my backwards hillbilly redneck family.  I can remember like yesterday watching her read, sigh, and pause to look at me.  Read 15 more pages.  Heavy sigh.  And look again, but disgusted 😂  Another chapter and look, even more disgusted. I'd just nod my head like \"yep, it's true. We be like that\" (she found no humor in this btw) another chapter followed by a burning hateful stare.  By the 2nd night she finished the book and we were basically divorced.\nJD Vance is an American hero",
