  {
    "id": "1816504073878999248",
    "text": "JD Vance’s “memoir, Hillbilly Elegy, contains a revealing anecdote about his childhood belief that he was gay. Influenced by a preacher’s condemnation of homosexuality, young Vance feared he was destined for hell simply because he disliked girls and cherished his friendship with another boy.”\n\n🍿",
