  {
    "id": "2014680131432763462",
    "text": "Why JD Vance would make a far better President in 2028 than Gavin Newsom:\n\n- **Working-Class Roots vs. Elite Privilege**  \nVance grew up in poverty, served in the Marines, and wrote *Hillbilly Elegy* to spotlight forgotten Americans. Newsom is a San Francisco multimillionaire who got his start through Getty family connections.\n\n- **Economic Record**  \nVance champions tariffs, manufacturing revival, and energy independence to bring jobs back to the heartland. Newsom presides over California’s exodus: highest poverty rate (when cost of living is factored), businesses fleeing high taxes and regulations, and skyrocketing energy costs from aggressive green mandates.\n\n- **Border & Public Safety**  \nVance prioritizes secure borders and law enforcement. Newsom’s California has sanctuary state policies, rising homelessness, and retail theft crises that have driven stores out of cities.\n\n- **Cultural Direction**  \nVance defends traditional American values and free speech. Newsom pushes progressive mandates on schools, gender policies, and COVID lockdowns long after most states moved on.\n\nAmerica needs a leader who understands struggle and puts citizens first—not a polished career politician managing decline in a one-party state.\n\nJD Vance 2028.🇺🇸🇺🇸🇺🇸",
